{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, this includes the 'risk' of 'detecting' especially when attempting to regulate the use of generative AI.",
    "This includes the inherent potential risk of detection tools which produce false positives or false negatives.",
    "In this context, the risk is that one detection tool suggests that the submitted text includes generative AI while another system produces an opposite verdict.",
    "The implicit concern is the emergence of academic McCarthyism, or a rebirth of the Salem Witch trials where accusations are made against the innocent with no viable means for response, recourse, or remedy.",
    "However, this is not the only case of this occurring, a recent article published in Scientific American, presented findings that suggests that one percent of scientific articles published in 2023 alone appeared to show signs of generative AI use (Stokel-Walker 2024)."
  ]
}